value.0: Overall, Smilodon are more robustly built than any othe cat, with particularly well-developed forelimbs and exceptionally long upper canine teeth. Its jaw has a bigger gape than that of other cats, and its upper canines are slender and fragile, being adapted for precision killing. The tail and ears are short to preserve body heat in the frozen tundra they usually dwell in.
Frozen Wastes: Manticore of Ice Hide

Thylacoleo has a very broad head and immensely powerful jaws. arge cutting premolars adapted to cutting flesh and cracking bone.

Thylacoleo is also distinguished by its front paws, whose semi-opposable thumbs are being used for either climbing trees or gripping onto prey.

Mastodons are shorter than elephants but are heavily built. Although the skull is lower and flatter and of generally simpler construction than that of elephants, it is similar in appearance. The ears are smaller and not as prominent as those of elephants due to the cold climate they are native to.
OOC ring for all bosses, to protect against the more popular spells for instant death.

Like rhinos, Elasmotherium had 3 working toes. Although they had much longer legs, so it may have galloped like a horse. Just, much slower and understandably so. It has a massive keratinous horn and a wooly coat over the body. A unique feature to the Elasmotherium is the presence of euhypsodonty (ever-growing or rootless molars)

Like other ground sloths it has a blunt snout, massive jaw and large, peg-like teeth. The hind limbs are plantigrade (flat-footed) and this, along with its stout tail, allows it to rear up into a semi-erect position to feed on tree leaves. The forelimbs has three highly developed claws that are used to strip leaves and tear off branches.

Titanis, also known as the Terror Bird, has an elongated skull ending in a thin, hooked beak. It is a large, flightless carnivorous bird.  It has a short tail and round body, with long and powerful legs. In fact, it also has very robust toes - and one of the strongest middle toes known for a Bird. It has very small, useless wings, that are very much locked in against the body.

Elephant birds are large sized birds (the largest reaching 3 metres (9.8 ft) tall in normal standing posture) that have vestigial wings, long legs and necks, with small heads relative to body size, which bear straight, thick conical beaks that are not hooked.

The main feature of glyptodons is their tortoise-like body armour that is made of bone segments called osteoderms or scutes. With this protection, they are armored like turtles, but unlike most turtles, can not withdraw their heads. Instead they have a bony cap on the top of their skull.

Macrauchenia patachonica live in cold and frozen regions. It resembles a bulky camel without a hump, with a long neck like that of a llama and a short trunk for a nose. The long neck does enable the herbivore to reach leaves on plants and bushes.

Toxodon is perhaps one of the strangest animals ever discovered.  lIt has a large muscular body and short stout legs with three functional toes, with most of the body weight being borne by the central toe. Toxodon has a very unusual gait, due to its peculiar proportions. It gallops to escape predators, but like a rhino, it relies more on its size as protection against predators.
